<topic id='element_death_cause_icd_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>Format / Length</dt>
        <dd>min an3 max an5</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_classification_code">CLINICAL CLASSIFICATION CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE</xref>
 is the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/international_classification_of_diseases_(icd).asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">International_Classification_of_Diseases_(ICD)</xref>
 code derived from the 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_death_cause_recorded_text">DEATH CAUSE RECORDED TEXT</xref>
 by the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">ONS</xref>
).  </p>
  <p>
The information for the following 
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE</xref>
 Data Elements is taken from the Medical Certificate of Cause of Death:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
I(a): 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code__immediate_condition_">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE (IMMEDIATE CONDITION)</xref>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
I(b): 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code__due_to_condition_">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE (DUE TO CONDITION)</xref>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
I(c): 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code__other_condition_">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE (OTHER CONDITION)</xref>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
II: 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code__contributing_condition_">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE (CONTRIBUTING CONDITION)</xref>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
Note: 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_death_cause_icd_code__underlying_condition_">DEATH CAUSE ICD CODE (UNDERLYING CONDITION)</xref>
 is the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/international_classification_of_diseases_(icd).asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">International_Classification_of_Diseases_(ICD)</xref>
 code derived by the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">ONS</xref>
) taken from the death certificate codes above.  </p>
  <p>For further information regarding the Medical Certificate of Cause of Death, see:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <p>
The 
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 document 
            <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-notes-for-completing-a-medical-certificate-of-cause-of-death"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Guidance for doctors completing Medical Certificates of Cause of Death in England and Wales</xref>
         </p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>
This document advises Doctors how to complete the Death Certificate and also contains information on how the 
                    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 code the text.          </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </li>
      <li/>
      <li>
         <p>
The 
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 website at: 
            <xref href="https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20160105231503/http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/guide-method/user-guidance/health-and-life-events/index.html"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Health and life events guidance and metadata</xref>
         </p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>See the Mortality metadata document. Annex A shows the Medical Certificate of Cause of Death.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </li>
  </ul>


